A senior high school teacher from Anshun city has been dubbed the ` luckiest wife in China ' after her soldier husband cooked her enough food to last for a year before he returned to service .
Husband Yin Yunfeng spent the last week of his annual holiday making all sorts of stir-fried dishes as well as about 1,000 dumplings as a way to show his love to his wife .
The husband is stationed in a regiment in Tibet and only gets to go home .